Because it is a more sensitive method than CV, determination of the luteolin concentration at the GQDs/GNPs/GCE was performed by DPV (Fig. 10
                        ). Under the optimal conditions, the calibration plot of oxidation peak current vs. luteolin concentration in phosphate buffer (pH 5.0) is shown in the inset of Fig. 10. The oxidative peak current increased linearly with luteolin concentration, and good linearity was observed in the range of 10 nM to 10 μM. The linear regression equation was I
                        pa (μA) = −(3.000 ± 0.03)C (μM) − (1.250 ± 0.05) (R = 0.996). The limit of detection, LOD, was 1.0 nM (calculated as 3σ/S, where σ is the blank standard deviation and S is the sensitivity of the calibration plot), which was comparable with the values reported by other research groups (Table 1
                        ). The results showed that the GQDs/GNPs/GCE exhibited a broader detection range and lower detection limit, indicating that it has good sensitivity for luteolin.
